  "text": "Multi-differentiation analysis of MSCs was performed as described previously with minor modifications [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Briefly, for osteogenic differentiation, MSCs at passage 3 were seeded into 24-well culture plates (1 ml/ well) at a density of 5 × 10 3 cells/cm 2 , grown in osteogenic induction medium for 14 days, and subjected to alkaline phosphatase (aLP) staining. The osteogenic induction medium consisted of culture medium, 0.1 µM dexamethasone, 10 mM β-glycerophosphate, and 50 µM ascorbic acid (Sigma-Aldrich, St. Louis, MO, USA). The osteogenic differentiation of MSCs was assayed by in situ aLP staining with a commercial kit (Sigma-aldrich).",
